  , issueCommentBody =
      "I'm actually not entirely sure this flag makes sense in `insert` at all. One option is to take it out of `insert` and instead add it to `replace` and `update` to control behavior as follows:\r\n\r\n```\r\ntable.get('does_not_exist').update(doc) # error\r\ntable.get('does_not_exist').update(doc, {insert: true}) # insert the document\r\ntable.get('does_not_exist').replace(doc) # error\r\ntable.get('does_not_exist').replace(doc, {insert: true}) # insert the document\r\n```\r\nThis would be more flexible and more consistent with how other systems do it."
